punches with Mr Ilya Constantinov, a leading nationalist.
It is now clear that both Mr Yeltsin and Mr Yegor Gaidar, the acting prime
minister, have decided to show a determined face to a hostile Congress which
so far hasfailed to display a united resolve in moving against them.
A committee representing 600 international banks yesterday granted the
