<HEADLINE>
FT  04 DEC 92 / International Company News: Dr Pepper IPO plan revived
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FIVE months after it dropped plans to go public because of unfavourable
stock market conditions, Dr Pepper/Seven-Up, the big US drinks group, has
revived its plan to sell shares in an initial public offering of common
stock.
But the size of the issue has been scaled down. The original plan was to
sell 38m shares between Dollars 17 and Dollars 18 each, but Dr Pepper said
it would sell only 20m shares, with a target price of Dollars 14 a share.
Over the summer a number of planned flotations were temporarily withdrawn or
abandoned because investor appetite for IPOs had waned. But shares have
performed well recently and demand for new stock has recovered.
</TEXT>
