Commons yesterday by Mr Michael Bates (C Langbaurgh).
He said it was estimated that small businesses - defined as those employing
fewer than 20 people - were currently owed some Pounds 145bn in unpaid
bills.
Mr Bates was given leave to introduce a private member's bill providing for
interest, similar to that normally awarded by the courts, to be paid when
contractual debts were not settled within the 30-day period.
