Sophia Loren, Roger Moore and Steffi Graf.
The campaign, aimed at visitors from the US and UK, is supported by British
Airways, American Express, the Forte hotel group, Harrods, Marks and
Spencer, the British Tourist Authority and several London museums and other
attractions.
Based on the slogan 'It's not only Londoners who love London', the campaign
will rely on newspaper and magazine advertising, direct mail and Prodigy - a
shopping service linking 1.8m personal computer users in the US.
The film and sports personalities have agreed to appear in the
advertisements and publicity material.
The London Tourist Board, one of the campaign organisers, said tourists
comprised 25 per cent of London Underground passengers, 40 per cent of West
End theatre audiences and 25 per cent of taxi passengers. They accounted for
17 per cent of Oxford Street spending.
More than 7 per cent of London's working population is employed in tourism,
which last year earned Pounds 4.4bn.
The Pounds 2.2m will be spent over six months. The campaign will then be
extended for an additional 2 1/2 years.
