<TEXT>
THE merger of KNP, VRG-Groep and Buhrmann-Tetterode into Europe's
second-biggest paper and packaging group will leave Canada's MacMillan
Bloedel with an important shareholding, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
MacMillan, 49 per cent held by Noranda Forest, Canada's biggest forest
products company, owns 30.5 per cent of KNP, worth around CDollars 300m
(USDollars 233m) at present prices.
The share exchange merger as proposed would leave MacMillan with about 17
per cent of the new company.
