<HEADLINE>
FT  02 DEC 92 / International Company News: Valeo makes Italian unit offer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
VALEO, the French car components group in which Mr Carlo De Benedetti is the
main shareholder through his Cerus holding company, is planning to buy out
the minority shareholders in its listed Italian subsidiary.
Shares in Valeo SpA were suspended in Milan and Turin yesterday pending
details of the offer from the French parent. Under the terms of the
transaction, which has still to be approved by Consob, Italy's stock market
and companies watchdog, Valeo will buy out the 43.6 per cent of Valeo SpA it
does not already own via a share swap and a balancing cash adjustment.
Details will not be released until Consob gives its approval. Somes brokers
criticised it because minority shareholders were not being offered a cash
alternative.
Valeo, which made net profits of FFr545m (Dollars 100m) on sales of
FFr19.87bn last year, said eliminating the minorities in its Italian
operation would boost net consolidated profits by between FFr1 and FFr2 a
share.
The group has sharply raised earnings this year in spite of weak demand.
</TEXT>
